README
======

So the process is as follows:

$ vim helloWorld.java
...
$ javac helloWorld.java
...
$ vim helloWorldUnitTest.java
...
$ javac -cp .:/usr/share/java/junit4.jar  helloWorldUnitTest.java 
...
$ java -cp .:/usr/share/java/junit4.jar org.junit.runner.JUnitCore  helloWorldUnitTest
JUnit version 4.12
.
Time: 0.003

OK (1 test)

$


Notes:
1. The -cp flag tells the java compiler and runtime to look for classes - long
version of the flag is -classpath so that the compiler can find the junit
library.

2. When the test suite is invoked the second argument after the classpath
argument is a reference to the package  org.junit.runner.JUnitCore  
